To the 2. Question he is answered, When thou hast brought forth the people out of Egypt, ye shall serve God upon this Mountain; that is, they shall here receive the Law, (for Horeb and Sinai are both one Mountain) and he shall be the Law-giver. And because there did still remain some Scruple in Moses, imagining that he who spoke with him might be onely some high Intelligence, which, though firm and durable, might have had a beginning;
he replies, If they shall say to me, What is his name? what shall I say unto them? To which he is answered, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
I am that I am: though the Grammaticall sense is, I will be what I will be, that is, I will be with you what I will ever be, alwaies the same, Eternall and Immutable. And here was manifestly declared to him what before was onely signified, as hath been said.

As they generally divide the World into three parts;
the Angelicall World, assisting about the Throne of God, the Celestial World, respecting the Sphears, and this Sublunary and Elementary World: so the House of God was distinguished into three parts or three degrees of Holiness gradually separated, semblably thereto; that is, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 the Holy of Holies,
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 the Palace, and 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 the Outer Court.
